{"author":{"id":"8b4e58f5679bcce787fd551e8e87fa9849dbb7627d4f14ea3898f84c8a9da805"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1448575320,"nonce":"V0atx1SfmODpBMSwXsP7ToZXs8g=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE1OTk5ODIwOA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/299#issuecomment-159998208"},"message":"Hi everyone,\n\njust an update concerning:\n1/ Mothur. We have, in the GUGGO Tool Shed, quite old Mothur (1.32) [toolshedized tools](http://toolshed.genouest.org/repository/view_repository?sort=name\u0026operation=view_or_manage_repository\u0026f-free-text-search=mothur\u0026id=66701dbe65507c8c) developped by colleagues from the CNRS / OSUR Biogenouest [Environmental genomics core facility](https://osur.univ-rennes1.fr/page.php?93) in partnership with GenOuest.\n\nI don't know if this can be, totally or in part, of interest for the Mothur community but I remember that the engineer who has working on it, Mathieu Bahin, have made large improvements of the existing (old) Mothur Galaxy tools.... Maybe someone from the \"Mothur Galaxy\" community (@IyadKandalaft ?) can efficiently evaluate this?\nAn introduction (on remote hackathon \u0026/or on metagenomics pipeline) can be of interest\n\n2/ Qiime. The Ifremer colleagues have developped, totally from scratch if I don't make mistakes, Galaxy tools using Qiime 1.9. They have used the qiimetogalaxy script to create automatically the basis of Galaxy descriptors.... Once again, maybe this can be of interest for the \"Qiime Galaxy\" community (@lparsons).... or not ;)","files":null}]}